ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Down-to-earth introductory algebraic number theory which essentially requires only linear algebra and some abstract algebra knowledge (including Galois theory). Good for advanced undergrads, and also for any grad students who don't know algebraic number theory too well.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Well certainly I learned some basic setting about algebraic number theory from this course, which is very interesting and good for any mathematician to know. However I'm not so sure if this will help my career directly, at least in my graduate studies.
